<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857P43/45</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1916, noon</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received March 26, 9 a.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1640. Your 1786,<note n="1" xml:id="d277fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_156">p.
                                    156</ref>.</note> February 2, 3 p. m. <hi rend="italic">Note
                                    verbale</hi> from the Sublime Porte dated March 7 states that
                                the <hi rend="italic">Persia</hi> was not sunk by a submarine flying
                                the flag of Turkey. The note adds that, <pb facs="0501" n="215" xml:id="pg_215"/> Inasmuch as all naval vessels acting under the
                                instructions of the Turkish Government must necessarily fly Ottoman
                                flag, it could not therefore have been an Ottoman submarine or one
                                acting under the instructions of the Turkish Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>